    title: "Museums in United States",
    type: "Web Mapping Application",
    typeKeywords: ["Map", "Mapping Site", "Online Map", "Web Map"],
    description:
      "<div style='font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Web&quot;, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:16px; margin:0px; padding:0px; clear:both; color:rgb(0, 0, 0);'><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; padding:0px; font-kerning:none; background-color:transparent; color:windowtext;'><font size='4' style='font-family:inherit;'><span style='font-family:Calibri, Calibri_EmbeddedFont, Calibri_MSFontService, sans-serif; margin:0px; padding:0px; font-variant-ligatures:none !important;'><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'>Museums have always been known for their educational and leisure value and for the contributions that they make to the tourism economy of any region. But in the current years, there has been a growing body of research that highlights the broader societal impacts of museums, particularly their potential positive impact on the social wellbeing of communities. The Institute of Museum and Library Services (IMLS), an independent federal agency that aims to support and empower America’s museums and libraries through research, grants, and policy development, in their recent studies, looks at the diverse ways in which museums promote social inclusion and wellbeing, particularly community health, economic wellbeing, and school effectiveness. Considering these studies based on museums’ engagement with several community concerns, the broader target audience of this Chart Viewer App</span><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'> includes researchers, journalists, practitioners, policymakers, and government agencies at all administrative levels. </span></span><span style='font-family:Calibri, Calibri_EmbeddedFont, Calibri_MSFontService, sans-serif; margin:0px; padding:0px;'> </span></font></p></div><div style='font-family:&quot;Segoe UI&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Web&quot;, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size:16px; margin:0px; padding:0px; clear:both; color:rgb(0, 0, 0);'><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; padding:0px; font-kerning:none; background-color:transparent; color:windowtext;'><span style='font-family:Calibri, Calibri_EmbeddedFont, Calibri_MSFontService, sans-serif; margin:0px; padding:0px; font-variant-ligatures:none !important;'><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'><font size='4' style='font-family:inherit;'><br /></font></span></span></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; padding:0px; font-kerning:none; background-color:transparent; color:windowtext;'><span style='font-family:Calibri, Calibri_EmbeddedFont, Calibri_MSFontService, sans-serif; margin:0px; padding:0px; font-variant-ligatures:none !important;'><font size='4' style='font-family:inherit;'><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'>The current version of this Instant App offers a generic overview of museums spread across the United States. It maps 7,000+ museums in the country and nine different bar charts that </span><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'>provide</span><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'> extra insight into the distribution of these museums by type, state, region, and revenue group. The map </span><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'>exhibits</span><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'> a clustered visualization of museums by type, including Art, History, and Science Museums, Children’s Museums, Arboretums, and Botanical Gardens. It comes with popups that </span><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'>provide</span><span style='font-family:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px;'> related cluster information - the count of museums and the predominant type of museum within the cluster, and feature information, including museum address, contact, and website URL. This publicly available dataset, created by the Institute of Museum and Library Services (IMLS), is a compilation of data from various public, non-profit, and third-party sources. The app highlights the newest enhancements of the Chart Viewer Template that allows the user to display up to three charts at once alongside the map and to expand either the charts or the map to be viewed in a full-screen mode.</span></font></span></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; font-size:12px; padding:0px; font-kerning:none; background-color:transparent; color:windowtext;'><span style='font-family:Calibri, Calibri_EmbeddedFont, Calibri_MSFontService, sans-serif; margin:0px; padding:0px; font-size:12pt; font-variant-ligatures:none !important;'><br /></span></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; font-size:12px; padding:0px; font-kerning:none; background-color:transparent; color:windowtext;'><span style='font-family:Calibri, Calibri_EmbeddedFont, Calibri_MSFontService, sans-serif; margin:0px; padding:0px; font-size:12pt; font-variant-ligatures:none !important;'>Data Source: </span><a href='https://www.imls.gov/research-evaluation/data-collection/museum-data-files' style='color:rgb(0, 121, 193); text-decoration-line:none; font-family:inherit;' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>Institute of Museum and Library Services, 2018</a></p></div>",
