    title: "Post-disaster Damage Assessment: Odisha, India",
    type: "Web Mapping Application",
    typeKeywords: ["Map", "Mapping Site", "Online Map", "Web Map"],
    description:
      "<p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:1.5rem; font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px;'><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>Coastal Odisha has faced several cyclonic events over the last two decades and is still recovering from the losses and impacts of the previous storms. The state's early warning systems and disaster preparedness have improved over the years because of which the loss of human life has reduced over the years. But its approach towards long-term recovery is still very limited.</font></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:1.5rem; font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px;'><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>This app can be used to collect regional and neighborhood level information post-disaster to understand the varying scales of damages caused and to create a database that can be further analyzed for initiating discussions on long-term recovery processes for the coastal region of the state. The data collection method can include field assessments and secondary methods, like documenting media reports. The app currently visualizes data collected during a field assessment conducted along National Highway 316 from Pipili to Puri, approximately three weeks post-Cyclone Fani, that hit the eastern coast of India on May 3, 2019.</font></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px;'></p><ol><li><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>Add and edit data by using the '<i>Edit'</i> tool. Damaged features have been categorized broadly into seven classes (as seen in the legend), which have been further subcategorized, for example, vegetation has been subcategorized as cropland and trees. While adding data to the app, choose the subcategory and fill in relevant information using the attribute data form. </font></li><li><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>To add a data point, use the '<i>Search</i>' tool to search for a location or use the '<i>Find my Location</i>' tool. </font></li><li><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>Use the '<i>Basemap Gallery</i>' to change the reference map while adding, updating, or viewing data.</font></li></ol>",
