    description:
      "<p><span style='background:white;'><font color='#000000'>Cost of housing\nis largely decided by the kind of place we live in! </font></span><span style='color:rgb(0, 0, 0);'>An annual report published by the Urban Reform Institute in\nTexas calculates an affordability score for several housing markets across the\nglobe based on median household income and median housing price. Any city with\na score above 5.1 is classified as unaffordable. Using the dataset published by\nthem this app visualizes and ranks the most and the least affordable housing\nmarkets of the world in the year 2022 and 2021.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style='background:white;'><font color='#000000'>Start exploring\nthe data by using the countdown sections to page through each location of this Countdown app. While\npaging through the locations in the countdown sections, the map will focus on\nthe extent that showcases that feature. Use the pin to compare feature to\nidentify relationships among the locations in the map.</font></span></p>",
