    name: null,
    title: "Mapping the Slums of Cape Town",
    type: "Web Mapping Application",
    typeKeywords: ["Map", "Mapping Site", "Online Map", "Web Map"],
    description:
      "<p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:1.5rem; font-size:16px; color:rgb(74, 74, 74); font-family:&quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif;'><span style='font-family:inherit; color:rgb(64, 64, 64);'><span style='font-family:Arial, sans-serif; background-image:initial; background-position:initial; background-size:initial; background-repeat:initial; background-attachment:initial; background-origin:initial; background-clip:initial;'><b><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>Introduction:</font></b></span></span></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:1.5rem; color:rgb(74, 74, 74); font-family:&quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:14px;'><span style='font-family:inherit; color:rgb(64, 64, 64);'><span style='font-family:Arial, sans-serif; background-image:initial; background-position:initial; background-size:initial; background-repeat:initial; background-attachment:initial; background-origin:initial; background-clip:initial; font-size:10.5pt;'>As people are increasingly migrating to urban areas, rise of slums have become a common phenomenon in most cities and metropolitan areas of the world. Most urban planners have come to realize that slums are not an isolated phenomenon and getting rid of them wholly is unachievable. So instead of eliminating such settlements from the urban fabric, they now try to focus their research and practice on improving the conditions of these settlements, which include access to basic infrastructure and services, availability of affordable housing and employment and land tenure security. On the other hand, many city governments across the globe still refuse to acknowledge the existence of slums, with their attitudes ranging from eviction to reluctant acceptance and upgradation. The biggest and most imperative challenge in this regard has been identifying and mapping slums due to the lack of official records and information in most cases.</span></span></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:1.5rem; font-size:16px; color:rgb(74, 74, 74); font-family:&quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif;'><span style='font-family:inherit; color:rgb(64, 64, 64);'><span style='font-family:Arial, sans-serif; background-image:initial; background-position:initial; background-size:initial; background-repeat:initial; background-attachment:initial; background-origin:initial; background-clip:initial;'><b><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>About the app:</font></b></span></span></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:1.5rem; color:rgb(74, 74, 74); font-family:&quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:14px;'><span style='font-family:inherit; color:rgb(64, 64, 64);'><span style='font-family:Arial, sans-serif; background-image:initial; background-position:initial; background-size:initial; background-repeat:initial; background-attachment:initial; background-origin:initial; background-clip:initial; font-size:10.5pt;'>This app provides an example of a data collection and mapping project that can evolve as a community participation project by involving citizens in the mapping of slums and urban services and amenities around them. The app and the geolocated information can be used to identify key issues and problems of the slum residents and help to design solutions for meeting their needs.</span></span></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:1.5rem; color:rgb(74, 74, 74); font-family:&quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:14px;'><span style='font-family:inherit; color:rgb(64, 64, 64);'><span style='font-family:Arial, sans-serif; background-image:initial; background-position:initial; background-size:initial; background-repeat:initial; background-attachment:initial; background-origin:initial; background-clip:initial; font-size:10.5pt;'>In 2018, 56.2% of the urban population (238 million) of Sub-Saharan Africa was living in slums (UN Stats, 2021). The app uses Cape Town in South Africa as an example, which is also home to one of the largest slums of the world, Khayelitsha. This app uses crowdsourced data from OpenStreetMap, and publicly available data published by the </span></span><a href='https://odp-cctegis.opendata.arcgis.com/' style='color:rgb(0, 121, 193); text-decoration-line:none; font-family:inherit;' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>City of Cape Town</a><span style='font-family:inherit; color:rgb(64, 64, 64);'><span style='font-family:Arial, sans-serif; background-image:initial; background-position:initial; background-size:initial; background-repeat:initial; background-attachment:initial; background-origin:initial; background-clip:initial; font-size:10.5pt;'>.</span></span></p><p style='margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:1.5rem; font-size:16px; color:rgb(74, 74, 74); font-family:&quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif;'><span style='font-family:inherit; color:rgb(64, 64, 64);'><span style='font-family:Arial, sans-serif; background-image:initial; background-position:initial; background-size:initial; background-repeat:initial; background-attachment:initial; background-origin:initial; background-clip:initial;'><b><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>How to use the app:</font></b></span></span></p><ol><li><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>Add and edit slums to the map by using the '<i>Edit'</i> tool. Use the '<i>Snapping</i>' tool while adding or editing the slum boundaries.</font></li><li><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'><font style='font-family:inherit;'>Urban Services and Amenities have been broadly categorized into four groups - Community Services, Emergency Services, Health Services and Transportation Amenities. While adding data, choose the type of amenity, use the </font>'<i>Edit'</i> tool to add it to the map and fill in relevant information using the attribute data form.  </font></li><li><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>To add a service or amenity, use the '<i>Search</i>' tool to search for a location or use the '<i>Find my Location</i>' tool. </font></li><li><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>Use the '<i>Basemap Gallery</i>' to change the reference map while adding, updating, or viewing data.</font></li><li><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>Use '<i>Layer List</i>' to enable or disable layers from the map.</font></li><li><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'>The slum layer in the Layer List comes with a '<i>Show Table</i>' option. Click on it to open and view the attribute table for the slums in Cape Town. </font></li></ol><div style='font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px;'><font size='3' style='font-family:inherit;'><br /></font></div><div style='font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px;'><font size='2' style='font-family:inherit;'><b>Data Source(s):</b> OpenStreetMap; <a href='https://odp-cctegis.opendata.arcgis.com/' style='color:rgb(0, 121, 193); text-decoration-line:none; font-family:inherit;' target='_blank' rel='nofollow ugc noopener noreferrer'>City of Cape Town Open Data Portal</a></font></div>",
