    title: "Pollution in the Ganges",
    type: "Web Mapping Application",
    typeKeywords: ["Map", "Mapping Site", "Online Map", "Web Map"],
    description:
      "<span style='font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px; color:rgb(51, 51, 51);'>An assemblage of untreated urban sewage, animal waste, pesticides, fertilizers, and industrial metals makes the Ganges one of the most polluted rivers in the world. However, flowing through the four Indian states of Uttarakhand, Uttar Pradesh, Bihar and West Bengal, it is still the source of life for 30% of India's population (~ 400 million). </span><p style='color:rgb(74, 74, 74); font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px;'><span style='color:rgb(51, 51, 51);'>This app visualizes the river's course and it's basin along with the cities and sources of pollution along it's banks.</span></p><p style='color:rgb(74, 74, 74); font-family:&quot;Avenir Next W01&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next W00&quot;, &quot;Avenir Next&quot;, Avenir, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size:16px;'><span style='background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);'><span style='margin-top:0px; margin-right:revert; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:revert; color:rgb(21, 21, 21); font-size:14px;'><b>Data Source:</b></span><span style='margin-top:0px; margin-right:revert; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:revert; font-weight:revert; color:rgb(21, 21, 21); font-size:14px;'> </span><span style='color:rgb(21, 21, 21); font-size:14px;'>Central Pollution Control Board (CPCB)</span></span><span style='color:rgb(51, 51, 51);'><br /></span></p>",
